202
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:42,680
-Kid, how was the exam? -Fine. Goodnight, grandma.

203
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:44,940
I suppose you don't expect

204
00:14:44,940 --> 00:14:46,760
me to clean up your friend's bed, right?

205
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,400
-No. -Goodnight.

206
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,640
Goodnight.

207
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:31,240
Pol and Bruno's exams are perfect.

208
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,720
Someone has stolen the Catalan exam.

209
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:39,560
Wait. They have perfect grades and you think that...

210
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:45,680
I asked Gloria to make 25 copies. She left them in the staffroom.

211
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,690
When I counted them, one was missing.

212
00:15:47,690 --> 00:15:49,520
At that moment, I didn't care much.

213
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:50,920
But she told me when she

214
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:53,520
left the copies on the table, at the staffroom,

215
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:57,280
there was only one person there.

216
00:15:58,080 --> 00:16:01,680
-Guess who. -Come on, Eugeni. We don't have time.

217
00:16:01,760 --> 00:16:03,600
You know perfectly who I'm talking about.

218
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:08,560
I corrected Bruno and Pol's exams and they got perfect marks.

219
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:11,760
